<HEADLINE>
FT  14 APR 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares staged a firm recovery from a sharp fall on Tuesday. Bullion looked
set to break back above the Dollars 380 an ounce level, while foreign
interest was seen in mining stocks.
The overall index put on 86 to 5,023, industrials 50 to 5,751 and the gold
index improved 69 to 1,985. De Beers rose R4.50 to R109.50, Vaal Reefs R12
to R414 and Iscor 10 cents to R3.15.
